@clouds
Feature: Add second-tier clouds

  Background:
    Given Test user is added

  Scenario Outline:
    Given I am logged in to mist.core
    When I click the button "Add cloud"
    Then I expect for "new-cloud-provider" panel to appear within max 10 seconds
    And I select "<provider>" from "new-cloud-provider" drop down
    And I expect for "new-cloud-provider" panel to disappear within max 10 seconds
    Then I expect for "cloud-add-fields" to be visible within max 10 seconds
    And I wait for 2 seconds
    When I use my "<credentials>" credentials
    And I click the button "Add"
    Then the "<provider>" cloud should be added within 60 seconds

    Examples: Providers
    | provider              | credentials  |
    | Azure                 | AZURE        |
    | DigitalOcean          | DIGITALOCEAN |
#    | GCE                   | GCE          |
    | Linode                | LINODE       |
    | EC2                   | EC2          |
#    | NephoScale            | NEPHOSCALE   |
#    | Rackspace             | RACKSPACE    |
#    | SoftLayer             | SOFTLAYER    |

  Scenario Outline:
    Given I am logged in to mist.core
    Then I wait for 100 seconds
